cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper deals with pruning strategies for deep neural networks, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. The focus is on multi-task networks, which are often used in computer vision applications such as face recognition (CelebA dataset is used in experiments). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses information theory and computation cost, which suggests possible sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
